    "Rotate Right": "Rotar dcha",
    "<html><head/><body><p>Set a custom gamma correction.</p><p>1.0 is default (disabled).<br/>&lt; 1.0 makes the image brighter.<br/>&gt; 1.0 makes the image darker. </p><p>1.8 was the default in KCC 9.1.0 and earlier.</p><p>Use if you want to make midtones darker.</p></body></html>": "<html><head/><body><p>Correcciones de Gama/Luz.</p></body></html>",
    "Custom gamma": "Gama manual",
    "<html><head/><body><p>By default, KCC maps the darkest pixel value to pure black (the black point.)</p><p>Extreme black point sets the black point to be the most common dark pixel value.</p><p>Useful when text is black but artwork is gray.</p></body></html>": "<html><head/><body><p>Por defecto KCC usa pix. oscuro como negro. Cmbialo por gris más obvio.</p></body></html>",
    "Extreme Black Point": "Forzar Color Negro",
